    </collaborator>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Boston Scientific Corporation</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the safety and efficacy of the implant of a ICD
      lead of defibrillation in the septum of the right ventricle
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The rate of success at implant and the positive clinical outcomes for the patients implanted
      with a lead of defibrillation at the septal site would make it possible to recommend this
      site as a &quot;new standard&quot; for implant of the defibrillation lead in the RV for ICD.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
